import.formalSyntax:
@import [ &lt;url&gt; | &lt;string&gt; ] [ layer | layer( &lt;layer-name&gt; ) ]? &lt;import-conditions&gt; ;
  &lt;url&gt; = url( &lt;string&gt; &lt;url-modifier&gt;* ) | src( &lt;string&gt; &lt;url-modifier&gt;* )
  &lt;layer-name&gt; = &lt;ident&gt; [ '.' &lt;ident&gt; ]*
  &lt;import-conditions&gt; = [ supports( [ &lt;supports-condition&gt; | &lt;declaration&gt; ] ) ]? &lt;media-query-list&gt;?
  &lt;supports-condition&gt; = not &lt;supports-in-parens&gt; | &lt;supports-in-parens&gt; [ and &lt;supports-in-parens&gt; ]* | &lt;supports-in-parens&gt; [ or &lt;supports-in-parens&gt; ]*
  &lt;supports-in-parens&gt; = ( &lt;supports-condition&gt; ) | &lt;supports-feature&gt; | &lt;general-enclosed&gt;
  &lt;supports-feature&gt; = &lt;supports-decl&gt;
  &lt;general-enclosed&gt; = [ &lt;function-token&gt; &lt;any-value&gt;? ) ] | [ ( &lt;any-value&gt;? ) ]
  &lt;supports-decl&gt; = ( &lt;declaration&gt; )

update.doc:
The <strong><code>update</code></strong> <a href="$MDN_URL$/Web/CSS">CSS</a> <a href="$MDN_URL$/Web/CSS/@media#media_features">media feature</a> can be used to test how frequently (if at all) the output device is able to modify the appearance of content once rendered.
<div class="code-example"><p class="example-header"><span class="language-name"><pre class="brush: css notranslate"><code>@media (update: &lt; none | slow | fast &gt;) {
  /* styles to apply if the update frequency of the output device is a match */
}
</code></pre></span></div>

